  Jessica is the 13th actress to achieve the Triple Crown of Acting, having won two Academy Awards, three Primetime Emmy Awards, and a Tony Award, along with a Screen Actors Guild Award and five Golden Globe Awards. The star made her professional film debut in Dino De Laurentiis's 1976 remake of King Kong, which led to her winning her first Golden Globe Award for New Star of the Year. A scantily dressed Jessica looks stunning in a number of action shots from the movie, where she can be seen cowering in fear of the giant ape. She went on to win a second Golden Globe and an Academy Award for her supporting role in the 1982 film Tootsie. She has also been nominated for Academy Awards in the films Frances (1982), Country (1984), Sweet Dreams (1985) and Music Books (1989).  Jessica finally won the Academy Award for Best Actress in 1994, when she played a bipolar housewife in the movie Blue Sky. She looks sensational as she lights up the screen in a ruby red outfit with lipstick to match as she poses for the role in the decades-old photographs. The Hollywood star has also turned out memorable performances in 1981’s The Postman Always Rings Twice, 1991’s Cape Fear and opposite Dennis Quaid in 1988’s Everybody's All-American. Aside from her successful film career, the actress has enjoyed a lot of popularity as an actress in American Horror Story between 2011 and 2019, for which she won her first Screen Actors Guild Award and first Critics Choice Award. Jessica Lange appears in the 1991 film Cape Fear at 10.40pm tonight on BBC One.   